WEBVTT

00:01.393 --> 00:03.227
<i> FIONA: Previously on</i>
The Cleaning Lady...

00:03.245 --> 00:04.895
There's a hospital in Mexico

00:04.913 --> 00:06.079
that will do Luca's surgery.

00:06.232 --> 00:07.581
<i> ARMAN: If you</i>
<i> could be ready by morning,</i>

00:07.733 --> 00:09.842
<i> I can take us there and back</i>
<i> by jet.</i>

00:10.069 --> 00:12.236
What is Arman doing in Mexico?

00:12.238 --> 00:14.071
He went to Mexico
to sell guns.

00:14.073 --> 00:15.255
I have to go.

00:15.332 --> 00:17.332
How will we get back
to the U.S. without you?

00:17.409 --> 00:19.018
Yeah, I got an informant
in the wind.

00:19.169 --> 00:22.170
All this time,
I've kept things sexy and fun,

00:22.248 --> 00:23.689
and you still had
to sneak around.

00:23.766 --> 00:26.007
-ARMAN: It's not true.
-Get out!

00:26.027 --> 00:29.010
<i> (suspenseful music)</i>

00:29.030 --> 00:36.035
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:42.859 --> 00:44.692
Arman!

00:44.770 --> 00:46.211
Armando!

00:48.440 --> 00:50.941
Arman!

00:50.943 --> 00:52.051
<i> Dios mío!</i>

00:53.445 --> 00:54.887
Arman! No, no!

00:54.963 --> 00:56.296
<i> Dios mío!</i>

00:56.298 --> 00:58.282
<i> -THONY: Arman? Arman?</i>
-NADIA: Wake up. Wake up!

00:58.300 --> 01:00.059
Please come back for me,
Armando.

01:01.395 --> 01:04.045
Stay with me.
Stay with me, Arman, please!

01:04.065 --> 01:06.732
<i> THONY:</i>
<i> Come back for me, Arman.</i>

01:06.883 --> 01:08.901
Come back for me, Arman.

01:09.052 --> 01:11.653
(speaks Spanish)

01:12.907 --> 01:14.364
(speaks Filipino)

01:16.726 --> 01:19.620
(grunting)

01:22.808 --> 01:24.750
(speaks Spanish)

01:24.901 --> 01:26.585
(echoing)
<i> Mi amor...</i>

01:30.649 --> 01:33.550
(speaking Spanish)

01:35.429 --> 01:36.470
<i> THONY: Arman?</i>

01:37.747 --> 01:38.597
Arman!

01:53.839 --> 01:56.690
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

01:56.842 --> 02:01.703
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:03.031 --> 02:05.624
(ambient background noise)

02:26.981 --> 02:29.398
(soft grunting)

02:35.639 --> 02:37.739
(distant, indistinct chatter)

02:53.899 --> 02:55.549
<i> Ay, mi amor.</i>

03:01.423 --> 03:03.849
-Shh, shh, shh.
-(speaking Spanish)

03:03.926 --> 03:06.059
<i>Estoy bien, estoy bien.</i>

03:11.007 --> 03:13.358
-Where are we?
<i> - Siéntate.</i>

03:13.510 --> 03:15.194
We are a couple of hours
out of town.

03:15.345 --> 03:18.322
I-I didn't know where to go.

03:20.275 --> 03:22.092
Look, Arman, I'm sorry
I said those things.

03:22.110 --> 03:24.761
I was so mad,
but I didn't mean it.

03:25.447 --> 03:27.522
-I didn't mean it.
-ARMAN: It's okay, it's okay.

03:27.599 --> 03:28.540
You're all right.

03:29.859 --> 03:30.709
You're okay.

03:34.623 --> 03:37.198
How long have I been out?

03:37.276 --> 03:39.718
In and out of it
for almost a week.

03:42.130 --> 03:43.630
Did Hayak call?

03:44.374 --> 03:47.559
I threw away our phones
but checked voicemail.

03:48.787 --> 03:49.519
Nothing.

03:50.305 --> 03:53.623
It had to have been Hayek.

03:53.642 --> 03:56.050
He must have found out
about the gun deal with Noah.

03:56.128 --> 03:57.903
Who else knew about it?

03:58.054 --> 03:59.738
Only Carlos.

04:02.076 --> 04:03.617
Any word from them?

04:04.653 --> 04:05.619
No.

04:08.064 --> 04:10.332
So you think Carlos told Hayek?

04:12.402 --> 04:15.629
What's important
is that you're alive...

04:19.576 --> 04:21.343
And we have each other.

04:23.839 --> 04:26.990
Marco, you should be
celebrating,

04:27.009 --> 04:28.100
not picking a fight.

04:28.251 --> 04:29.584
Luca had surgery
a week ago.

04:29.661 --> 04:31.603
Why hasn't she told me
when my son is coming home?

04:31.680 --> 04:34.014
Thony told you they want Luca
to stay a little longer

04:34.090 --> 04:35.691
to recover.

04:36.926 --> 04:40.028
Chris, time to get up!

04:41.282 --> 04:42.839
Go bang on your brother's door,
will you?

04:42.858 --> 04:43.699
He'll just yell at me.

04:45.694 --> 04:49.029
Chris, you're gonna be late
for school again!

04:49.105 --> 04:50.330
Get a move on.

04:54.986 --> 04:56.378
Why are you dressed
like that?

04:58.299 --> 05:00.716
I'm going with you
to see that lawyer.

05:02.194 --> 05:04.044
I'm just gonna ask
for an extension.

05:04.196 --> 05:06.546
Mom, he's scamming you.

05:07.366 --> 05:10.033
I went over the fees.
You're getting ripped off.

05:10.035 --> 05:12.552
W-what are you talking about?
I--

05:12.646 --> 05:15.981
Look, anyone can download
the DACA application for free.

05:16.132 --> 05:18.208
Filing it is $495.

05:18.301 --> 05:22.045
That lawyer guy
is charging you 795.

05:22.047 --> 05:23.471
Let me see this.

05:23.549 --> 05:25.824
Yeah, and he's charging you
an expediting fee of $400.

05:25.975 --> 05:27.326
That's not even a thing.

05:27.477 --> 05:28.735
What the hell?

05:28.887 --> 05:31.830
Yeah, he's--he's taking
advantage of you.

05:32.057 --> 05:33.540
Wouldn't be the first time.

05:35.060 --> 05:36.501
I have to go with you.

05:36.653 --> 05:39.896
-No, you-you can't skip school.
-Yeah, I can, okay?

05:39.915 --> 05:41.340
This is my future.

05:42.401 --> 05:44.593
I'm coming.

05:47.255 --> 05:48.847
<i> Buenos días,</i> Thony.

05:48.998 --> 05:50.073
Good morning, Julio.

05:50.092 --> 05:51.925
How's my favorite patient
doing?

05:52.077 --> 05:53.185
Luca's sleeping, eating.

05:53.261 --> 05:55.169
Um, his PELD scores show that

05:55.189 --> 05:57.022
his body's not rejecting
the liver, so...

05:57.099 --> 05:58.415
I'm so happy to hear that.

05:58.433 --> 06:00.083
And I saw that your donor,
Dara,

06:00.085 --> 06:01.509
was discharged
from the hospital?

06:01.528 --> 06:03.253
Yeah, yes. This morning.

06:03.255 --> 06:05.922
Uh, she's with Luca right now.

06:05.924 --> 06:07.199
Have a good one.

06:07.350 --> 06:09.776
Thony, before you go,
I'm afraid the credit card

06:09.928 --> 06:12.854
we have on a file
belonging to Arman Morales--

06:12.931 --> 06:13.997
it was declined.

06:15.209 --> 06:16.266
Really?

06:17.436 --> 06:21.213
Um, well, he's-he's gone
to the States for business,

06:21.289 --> 06:23.215
-but I could--
-That's okay.

06:23.291 --> 06:24.216
After all you went through,

06:24.367 --> 06:26.276
we can certainly
comp you a night,

06:26.294 --> 06:28.111
but we have another patient
arriving tomorrow.

06:28.130 --> 06:29.963
So we'll need you
to check out by then.

06:30.115 --> 06:32.391
-I'm sure you understand.
-Of course.

06:32.542 --> 06:35.468
I can recommend some very nice
hotels that are close by.

06:35.621 --> 06:38.138
If you like,
I could arrange that.

06:38.214 --> 06:40.315
No, thank you.
We're going home.

06:43.795 --> 06:45.720
My turn.

06:45.797 --> 06:46.905
Maybe your turn.

06:47.056 --> 06:47.981
A real latte.

06:48.057 --> 06:49.741
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

06:49.893 --> 06:50.967
(gasps)

06:51.060 --> 06:52.802
Wait, are you
peeking at my hand?

06:52.821 --> 06:54.061
No, I'm not.

06:54.081 --> 06:57.231
I saw you.
You're a cheater-weeter.

06:57.309 --> 07:00.827
-No, I'm not.
-(both laugh)

07:00.979 --> 07:02.570
How are you feeling, Dara?

07:02.648 --> 07:05.090
Just a little sore,
but weirdly good.

07:05.241 --> 07:06.758
Like, I could
have been giving pieces

07:06.910 --> 07:08.093
of my liver this whole time.

07:08.244 --> 07:09.319
Who knew?

07:09.321 --> 07:12.597
-I'm happy to hear that.
-(phone buzzing)

07:17.253 --> 07:19.679
I'll be right back.

07:19.831 --> 07:20.897
Okay.

07:21.683 --> 07:23.683
-Hello?
<i> -ARMAN: Thony.</i>

07:23.760 --> 07:25.944
Oh my God, Arman.

07:26.171 --> 07:28.780
(softly)
I thought you were dead.

07:28.932 --> 07:30.615
Are you okay?

07:30.767 --> 07:32.284
Yeah, I'm alive.

07:32.360 --> 07:33.285
<i> THONY:</i>
<i> What happened?</i>

07:34.529 --> 07:37.038
Someone tried to blow up
my car with me in it.

07:38.183 --> 07:40.033
Where are you now?

07:40.185 --> 07:41.460
Somewhere between
Vegas and Reno.

07:41.611 --> 07:44.463
I'm laying low
until I figure things out.

07:48.284 --> 07:50.860
But Thony, I'm not able
to come get you right now.

07:50.879 --> 07:53.196
I-I understand.

07:53.215 --> 07:55.724
Um, what should I do?

07:57.385 --> 07:58.643
<i> ARMAN:</i>
<i> I have a contact in Tecate</i>

07:58.795 --> 08:01.480
<i> who can arrange fake passports</i>
<i> for you and Luca.</i>

08:04.042 --> 08:04.849
How is he, by the way?

08:04.926 --> 08:06.710
He's doing great.

08:06.728 --> 08:08.445
They're gonna release him soon.

08:09.731 --> 08:10.897
You did it.

08:10.991 --> 08:12.565
No,<i> we</i> did it.

08:12.718 --> 08:15.994
It hadn't been for you
bringing us here.

08:17.405 --> 08:20.481
But, um, we're gonna
have to check out soon,

08:20.501 --> 08:23.460
and your credit card's
been declined.

08:24.505 --> 08:26.153
I can't access my money
right now,

08:26.231 --> 08:27.506
but my guy'll
cover the passports,

08:27.582 --> 08:30.425
and we have border agents
in our back pocket.

08:32.662 --> 08:34.237
I'll text you
where you need to go.

08:34.256 --> 08:35.739
<i> I'll be in touch.</i>

08:35.757 --> 08:36.740
Okay.

08:36.758 --> 08:42.078
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:42.080 --> 08:44.505
That was her, wasn't it?

08:44.525 --> 08:47.008
I left Thony and her son
stranded in Mexico.

08:47.102 --> 08:48.676
I need help
to get them back safe.

08:48.695 --> 08:50.103
That's all.

08:50.255 --> 08:52.364
He got his surgery,
her little boy?

08:53.608 --> 08:54.324
Yeah, he did.

08:55.369 --> 08:57.610
He's recovering.
He's gonna be all right.

08:57.763 --> 09:00.288
Okay, good.

09:01.542 --> 09:02.874
And now that her kid
is gonna be okay,

09:03.026 --> 09:05.252
you won't need
to help her anymore, will you?

09:06.362 --> 09:09.714
We have a second chance,
Arman,

09:09.791 --> 09:12.008
but you need to put
our marriage first.

09:14.296 --> 09:16.054
If you wanna be in my life,

09:16.131 --> 09:18.598
you have to cut
Thony out of yours.

09:31.479 --> 09:33.146
What's taking so long?

09:33.222 --> 09:36.057
Mr. Jennings has a really
busy schedule today.

09:36.076 --> 09:38.326
Next time you might wanna
make an appointment.

09:39.896 --> 09:41.079
FIONA:
Um, uh,

09:41.156 --> 09:43.081
if you could please
tell him again

09:43.158 --> 09:44.974
that we're still out here
that...

09:44.993 --> 09:47.502
I already did, twice.

09:52.742 --> 09:55.760
(indistinct chatter)

10:06.832 --> 10:10.025
(upbeat music playing,
singing in Spanish)

10:15.857 --> 10:19.200
<i> Buenos días.</i>
<i> Martín, por favor?</i>

10:22.530 --> 10:24.164
You wait here.

10:26.442 --> 10:29.461
Excuse me, Martín?

10:29.612 --> 10:31.087
Um, Arman sent me.

10:32.799 --> 10:34.257
-Thony?
-Yes.

10:35.861 --> 10:36.801
You bring your little boy?

10:36.953 --> 10:38.803
Mm-Hmm. He's in the store.

10:38.955 --> 10:40.639
Bring him back.

10:40.790 --> 10:42.641
Okay.

10:42.792 --> 10:46.536
<i> (vocalist singing in Spanish)</i>

10:46.554 --> 11:03.586
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:04.313 --> 11:06.147
-Country of origin?
-THONY: Cambodia for me.

11:06.166 --> 11:09.042
The Philippines for my son.
That's our home.

11:09.911 --> 11:11.819
What about her?

11:11.838 --> 11:13.421
THONY:
She's an American citizen.

11:16.418 --> 11:18.251
She could be the boy's mother.

11:18.327 --> 11:20.420
They don't usually inspect
children's passports

11:20.572 --> 11:23.098
that carefully
after they scan the parent's.

11:29.597 --> 11:30.438
Yeah.

11:31.674 --> 11:34.359
You can put her last name
on his passport.

11:34.510 --> 11:35.402
Oum. O-U-M.

11:36.679 --> 11:37.845
I'll change it now.

11:37.864 --> 11:41.533
Our agent...

11:41.684 --> 11:43.201
Guillermo Sanchez--

11:43.278 --> 11:45.019
he's expecting you.

11:45.096 --> 11:46.705
He's in booth number two.

11:46.856 --> 11:48.206
It's his last shift
of the week,

11:48.357 --> 11:49.708
so if you don't get through,

11:49.859 --> 11:51.935
you'll have to wait
until next week.

11:51.937 --> 11:53.937
We have to leave today.

11:53.939 --> 11:55.547
I'll be quick.
You have two hours.

11:55.698 --> 11:58.133
His shift ends at noon.

11:59.945 --> 12:02.870
<i> (tense music)</i>

12:02.948 --> 12:05.465
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:05.617 --> 12:08.393
(border patrol radio chatter)

12:10.897 --> 12:13.565
(indistinct chatter)

12:17.720 --> 12:20.029
(dog barking)

12:22.391 --> 12:23.800
PATROL WORKER: Yeah,
that's good to go. All right.

12:23.818 --> 12:25.744
Move up, please.

12:27.155 --> 12:29.414
PATROL WORKER:
Ma'am, please step forward.

12:30.992 --> 12:32.584
(indistinct chatter)

12:32.660 --> 12:34.502
TRAVELER: No opening yet?

12:40.594 --> 12:41.818
This is B.S.

12:41.820 --> 12:43.011
(stammers)

12:48.676 --> 12:51.394
-What?
-That's him, right?

12:52.755 --> 12:53.980
It sure is.

12:55.500 --> 12:56.349
Come on.

12:56.501 --> 13:03.281
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:09.697 --> 13:12.123
Hi, Mr. Jennings.
Remember us?

13:13.868 --> 13:15.442
Uh, sure.

13:15.520 --> 13:18.946
Yeah, that's what I thought.
We're your clients.

13:18.965 --> 13:20.799
You promised my son
a path to citizenship.

13:20.950 --> 13:22.658
You got my money
and then ghosted us.

13:22.694 --> 13:25.804
And you charged us bogus fees,
like a DACA expediting fee.

13:25.955 --> 13:27.288
There's no such thing.

13:27.307 --> 13:28.973
So we're going to find
another lawyer,

13:29.050 --> 13:30.124
and I want my money back.

13:30.218 --> 13:32.552
Why don't we discuss this
in my office?

13:32.704 --> 13:35.705
Have you even filed
any of his paperwork yet?

13:35.723 --> 13:37.707
I'd-I'd have to look.

13:37.725 --> 13:39.225
(scoffs)
That's a no.

13:39.302 --> 13:41.653
In my business,
if you don't work,

13:41.804 --> 13:43.563
you don't get paid.

13:43.715 --> 13:46.232
And besides that, I don't want
someone representing my son

13:46.309 --> 13:48.827
who doesn't give a crap.

13:48.903 --> 13:51.220
Okay? So give me back
my money now,

13:51.239 --> 13:53.222
or I will take you to court
for charging fees

13:53.241 --> 13:55.741
for services that were
never rendered or, hell,

13:55.894 --> 13:57.335
that doesn't even exist.

13:59.322 --> 14:00.746
Hey.

14:00.823 --> 14:02.732
If you think I won't...

14:02.750 --> 14:05.093
try me.

14:10.183 --> 14:13.667
Fine.
I'll issue a refund check.

14:13.687 --> 14:14.853
Let's walk over to billing.

14:15.004 --> 14:18.106
Wonderful.
Nice meeting you all.

14:20.935 --> 14:21.934
DARA:
What's wrong?

14:21.936 --> 14:24.136
It looks like
you're freaking out.

14:24.214 --> 14:26.489
We have less than ten minutes
before the shift change.

14:28.034 --> 14:30.118
Why won't this line move?

14:31.446 --> 14:34.539
OFFICER: This group
move to lane number three.

14:34.616 --> 14:35.932
Let's go.<i> Número tres.</i>

14:35.934 --> 14:37.600
(speaks Spanish)

14:37.619 --> 14:40.453
(dog barking)

14:40.605 --> 14:47.093
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:48.963 --> 14:50.179
Listen, Dara...

14:52.117 --> 14:54.541
I had Luca's passport made
in your last name.

14:54.619 --> 14:55.468
What? Why?

14:55.544 --> 14:57.954
Because you're
an American citizen.

14:57.956 --> 14:59.063
If you show
your passport first,

14:59.140 --> 15:00.732
they might not
even look at his.

15:00.883 --> 15:02.716
But wait, where are you
going to be?

15:02.794 --> 15:04.027
Behind you.

15:07.298 --> 15:09.982
If we get separated,
you're going without me.

15:10.135 --> 15:12.243
Luca needs to get home
to rest.

15:13.396 --> 15:17.156
Okay, here's some money
for a car rental.

15:17.308 --> 15:20.209
If you feel tired, there's
enough for a hotel tonight.

15:22.480 --> 15:24.571
If you need anything else,
just call Fiona.

15:24.591 --> 15:27.817
But if he shows any signs
he's not feeling well,

15:27.835 --> 15:30.303
you take him to a hospital
immediately.

15:33.266 --> 15:34.490
I don't know.

15:34.583 --> 15:36.008
Maybe we should do this
another day together.

15:36.161 --> 15:37.952
You gonna be fine, Dara.

15:38.029 --> 15:41.514
You're so good.
So good with him.

15:41.666 --> 15:43.232
- Go ahead.

15:44.427 --> 15:47.111
Hey, baby.

15:47.263 --> 15:51.115
It is so boring
to wait in line, isn't it?

15:51.267 --> 15:52.508
You wanna play a game?

15:52.527 --> 15:54.619
Yeah? Okay.

15:54.696 --> 15:59.348
So you see that man
over there in the booth?

15:59.350 --> 16:01.608
Once you get to him,
you're gonna pretend

16:01.628 --> 16:03.202
Dara is your mommy.

16:03.354 --> 16:05.296
Okay?

16:05.448 --> 16:06.372
Why?

16:06.466 --> 16:07.690
Because it's a game!

16:07.709 --> 16:11.527
And if we get separated, um,

16:11.546 --> 16:16.699
we're gonna have to race to see
who gets back first, right?

16:16.718 --> 16:18.726
-Yeah.
-Okay.

16:20.981 --> 16:21.887
GUILLERMO:
Next!

16:21.964 --> 16:29.112
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:40.649 --> 16:41.499
Next.

17:02.671 --> 17:03.771
Next.

17:06.934 --> 17:08.735
-Guillermo, you're relieved.
-Okay.

17:10.030 --> 17:11.754
Did you--did you
stamp the passport?

17:11.756 --> 17:18.745
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:28.565 --> 17:30.006
You have two options.

17:31.700 --> 17:33.885
I can call my supervisor
over to come look at this,

17:34.036 --> 17:35.536
or you can walk away.

17:35.613 --> 17:38.181
Using a forged document
is a federal crime.

17:42.562 --> 17:45.379
Mommy!

17:45.398 --> 17:47.473
Mommy, Mommy!

17:47.625 --> 17:50.643
Mommy!
Mommy!

17:50.795 --> 17:53.813
-Excuse me.
-Mommy!

17:53.965 --> 17:58.201
Mommy. Mommy!

18:02.990 --> 18:04.916
(touch tones dialing)

18:05.067 --> 18:08.644
(line ringing)

18:08.663 --> 18:11.147
<i> GARRETT: What the hell</i>
<i> you doing in Mexico?</i>

18:11.149 --> 18:12.423
How do you know that?

18:12.500 --> 18:14.258
GARRETT:
Let's try this again, huh?

18:14.410 --> 18:17.452
I'm Special Agent
Garrett Miller, FBI.

18:17.454 --> 18:19.580
You are Thony De La Rosa,
my informant,

18:19.599 --> 18:21.248
<i> which means you don't even</i>
<i> cross the street</i>

18:21.267 --> 18:23.584
<i> without me knowing about it.</i>
<i> What are you doing in Mexico?</i>

18:23.661 --> 18:25.252
I came here to get a surgery
for my son,

18:25.271 --> 18:26.587
and it was successful,

18:26.606 --> 18:28.523
so don't ask me to apologize,
okay?

18:30.593 --> 18:32.110
Now I need your help
getting back.

18:32.261 --> 18:34.520
Why didn't Arman
bring you back?

18:34.672 --> 18:36.355
You went with him, right?

18:36.507 --> 18:38.991
Can you get me
across the border or not?

18:40.120 --> 18:42.245
Does Luca need help
getting across too?

18:44.015 --> 18:45.848
No, it's just me.

18:45.867 --> 18:47.291
Are you safe?

18:47.368 --> 18:50.086
Yes. I just wanna go home.

18:51.947 --> 18:52.964
Let it go quick.

18:54.709 --> 18:56.634
Okay. Okay.

19:01.382 --> 19:03.123
Nope--that--

19:03.143 --> 19:04.267
-(laughs)
-Try again.

19:06.053 --> 19:09.538
(phone buzzes)

19:09.540 --> 19:11.874
Thony, how are you?

19:11.876 --> 19:14.068
Hi. I'm good. I'm good.

19:15.730 --> 19:17.989
Luca and Dara
are on their way back.

19:18.065 --> 19:19.973
What do you mean?
Why aren't you with them?

19:19.993 --> 19:21.400
Is that Thony?
Let me talk to her.

19:21.552 --> 19:23.018
<i> THONY: Well, Dara has</i>
<i> an American passport,</i>

19:23.020 --> 19:24.996
so she crossed with Luca.

19:25.223 --> 19:27.390
But, uh,
but when it was my turn--

19:27.408 --> 19:28.815
Oh, my God, did they
arrest you at the border?

19:28.835 --> 19:31.060
<i> THONY:</i>
<i> No, Fi, let me finish.</i>

19:31.078 --> 19:33.820
Garrett's gonna get me across.
It's gonna be okay.

19:33.898 --> 19:35.289
Let me talk to her.

19:35.366 --> 19:36.507
<i> THONY:</i>
<i> I can't talk to Marco now.</i>

19:36.659 --> 19:37.917
What's going on, Thony?

19:38.069 --> 19:39.010
I was talking to Fiona.

19:39.086 --> 19:40.494
Put it on speaker.

19:40.513 --> 19:41.846
Where are you?

19:42.164 --> 19:46.409
I'm still in Mexico, but Luca
is on his way home with Dara.

19:46.427 --> 19:48.911
So you're staying in Mexico
with him?

19:48.930 --> 19:50.246
Your boss? Is that it?

19:50.248 --> 19:52.932
I'm stuck here alone, okay?

19:53.084 --> 19:54.508
Put Fiona back on.

19:54.585 --> 19:56.694
Whatever you can tell her,
you can tell me.

19:56.845 --> 19:58.011
<i> THONY:</i>
<i> I'll call you later.</i>

19:58.031 --> 19:59.697
No, don't-don't hang up on--

19:59.774 --> 20:06.621
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:11.285 --> 20:12.960
Anything?

20:14.047 --> 20:16.464
Okay. Thanks.

20:18.793 --> 20:19.884
They can't help you.

20:20.035 --> 20:21.277
Why the hell not?

20:21.295 --> 20:22.778
I don't know, Garrett.

20:22.780 --> 20:25.556
Maybe more people than just me
are tired of your games.

20:25.708 --> 20:28.634
We have a crucial informant who
is stuck in another country.

20:28.711 --> 20:30.786
Will really no one in the
Bureau help me get her across?

20:30.805 --> 20:32.955
It's nothing to do
with the Bureau.

20:32.974 --> 20:34.381
She's on Homeland Security's
watch list

20:34.400 --> 20:36.383
after that stunt
you pulled with your ICE raid.

20:36.461 --> 20:38.477
We have satellite bureaus
in Mexico.

20:38.629 --> 20:41.239
Just make a few damn calls,
have her escorted across.

20:41.466 --> 20:42.531
Done. Easy.

20:43.801 --> 20:45.076
What?

20:45.227 --> 20:46.318
You.

20:46.395 --> 20:49.455
It's like watching
evolution in reverse.

20:53.828 --> 20:55.327
What about getting her an SPBP?

20:55.480 --> 20:58.631
She doesn't qualify now because
she's deemed for deportation.

21:00.242 --> 21:03.486
I screwed up, okay?
Fully own it.

21:03.579 --> 21:06.764
Now can you please get past it
and just help me?

21:06.841 --> 21:09.675
Look, without Thony's help,
we can kiss this case goodbye.

21:09.827 --> 21:12.103
ATF walks away with the guns.
We get nothing.

21:12.254 --> 21:13.178
Garrett.

21:13.331 --> 21:15.982
Facts, Katie.
I'm just stating facts.

21:17.518 --> 21:19.092
I mean, we must have
a border liaison

21:19.112 --> 21:21.320
who can release the skids
and let us cross.

21:23.265 --> 21:27.618
Russo, look at me.
She is crucial to this case.

21:27.695 --> 21:31.289
Without Thony, we are not
gonna nab these guys.

21:32.107 --> 21:33.332
You know that.

21:34.276 --> 21:36.352
I'll keep making calls.

21:36.354 --> 21:39.297
Okay. So can I head down?

21:40.300 --> 21:44.117
As a civilian.
No badge, no gun.

21:44.195 --> 21:45.711
<i> Comprende?</i>

21:45.863 --> 21:46.971
<i>Comprende.</i>

21:48.533 --> 21:51.142
No, I don't want you
to do this.

21:51.293 --> 21:52.368
This is no way
to live, Nadia.

21:52.386 --> 21:55.128
We have no money.
We can't go home.

21:55.206 --> 21:58.065
(both speaking Spanish)

21:58.818 --> 22:00.609
I have to face Hayak.

22:01.712 --> 22:03.321
He's way too dangerous.

22:04.231 --> 22:05.656
He knows he didn't kill me.

22:07.160 --> 22:09.160
I'm not safe now.
Wherever we go.

22:09.236 --> 22:12.330
<i> (apprehensive music)</i>

22:12.406 --> 22:16.075
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:16.227 --> 22:18.669
(speaking Spanish)

22:18.821 --> 22:20.004
Stay here. I'll be back.

22:20.081 --> 22:22.673
Think about
what you're doing.

22:22.900 --> 22:24.467
Oh, I have.

22:35.021 --> 22:38.064
(engine turns, revs)

22:40.918 --> 22:44.070
(tires screech)

22:50.611 --> 22:54.121
(radio chatter)

22:55.433 --> 22:57.933
GARRETT: I've been on the road
for seven hours.

22:57.935 --> 22:59.043
Still nothing?
No one will help?

22:59.194 --> 23:01.379
I tried--
it's too much paperwork

23:01.455 --> 23:03.881
for anyone to touch right now.

23:04.884 --> 23:07.093
All right, so what?
I'm flying solo?

23:08.129 --> 23:10.796
No, you are hanging tight

23:10.948 --> 23:14.133
<i> until I can do this</i>
<i> through the correct channels.</i>

23:14.285 --> 23:16.543
Okay, great. Thanks.

23:16.621 --> 23:18.378
<i> (upbeat music)</i>

23:18.398 --> 23:20.139
<i> (vocalist singing in Spanish)</i>

23:20.291 --> 23:23.792
(indistinct chatter)

23:23.811 --> 23:26.645
He loses everything.
(laughs)

23:26.722 --> 23:28.631
Oh, the look in his eyes.

23:28.633 --> 23:29.990
-Hayak.
-I was--

23:33.395 --> 23:34.970
Arman.

23:34.972 --> 23:37.081
Mind if we have a word?

23:38.476 --> 23:41.401
Sure. Um, excuse me.
(chuckles)

23:41.403 --> 23:42.628
Enjoy yourself.

23:46.926 --> 23:48.217
You okay?

23:49.244 --> 23:51.095
Vida, the grandkids.

23:51.246 --> 23:52.263
What are you talking about?

23:52.490 --> 23:53.931
Someone tried to kill me,
Hayak.

23:54.008 --> 23:55.749
What?

23:55.826 --> 23:58.102
Now I'm worried they're coming
after you next.

23:58.179 --> 24:00.329
Do you know who it was?

24:00.331 --> 24:01.605
I mean, it had to have
been Los Norteños.

24:01.682 --> 24:03.849
They wanted to buy
a bunch of guns from us,

24:04.001 --> 24:06.168
but their offer
was just too low.

24:06.187 --> 24:07.836
But you don't have proof.

24:07.855 --> 24:10.522
No, but its fits their M.O.
Bunch of hotheads

24:10.599 --> 24:13.159
couldn't get
a simple job done properly.

24:15.437 --> 24:17.079
-HAYAK: Good.
-Lucky for me.

24:18.365 --> 24:20.032
Yeah.

24:20.184 --> 24:22.442
How's Nadia? Is she okay?

24:22.520 --> 24:24.853
Yeah, she's worried,
but she's okay.

24:24.872 --> 24:26.464
That's terrible.

24:28.617 --> 24:31.677
You know, something good
came out of it, Hayak.

24:33.197 --> 24:35.197
I was able to negotiate
a higher price for the guns

24:35.199 --> 24:36.957
with a new buyer.

24:36.976 --> 24:38.884
I mean, even if you sold
these things piecemeal,

24:39.036 --> 24:41.395
you could never even
get close to 6 million.

24:42.464 --> 24:44.315
You're getting 6?

24:44.466 --> 24:46.650
Yeah.
Yeah, that's what I negotiated.

24:46.802 --> 24:49.636
I didn't want to tell you until
I had this guy Noah vetted.

24:49.655 --> 24:52.531
He's a survivalist type,
but he checked out.

24:53.567 --> 24:55.475
Where are the guns now?

24:55.495 --> 24:57.703
They're in a farmhouse.
Hector was watching them.

24:58.981 --> 25:01.081
But I can't get ahold
of Carlos.

25:03.151 --> 25:05.744
Have you heard from him?

25:05.821 --> 25:06.962
No, I haven't.

25:08.415 --> 25:09.398
Hmm.

25:09.416 --> 25:12.325
<i> (tense music)</i>

25:12.419 --> 25:15.495
Well, I'll, uh,
I'll get ahold of Hector,

25:15.515 --> 25:16.588
and then I'll reach out
to Noah

25:16.665 --> 25:18.849
and make sure
he is still on board.

25:19.001 --> 25:20.392
Sounds good.

25:23.080 --> 25:25.397
Thank God you're alive, son.

25:28.361 --> 25:32.029
You know, honestly,
I've never felt better.

25:35.426 --> 25:36.275
Good.

25:36.427 --> 25:43.165
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:51.366 --> 25:52.716
Let's go.

25:54.554 --> 25:58.371
You know what?
Um, it's almost 10:00.

25:58.449 --> 25:59.615
I've been driving all day.

25:59.633 --> 26:01.392
Why don't we just get
a couple of hotel rooms?

26:01.468 --> 26:02.951
I can drive.

26:02.953 --> 26:06.638
Or we leave tomorrow,

26:06.715 --> 26:09.124
and you'll be home
before dinnertime.

26:09.143 --> 26:10.475
Luca just had
a liver transplant.

26:10.552 --> 26:11.885
He needs to be
closely monitored

26:11.962 --> 26:14.530
by a doctor, which is me--
let's go.

26:23.231 --> 26:24.323
I'm sorry,
I should have told you

26:24.475 --> 26:25.824
about leaving the country.

26:25.901 --> 26:29.903
Well, let's not rehash it.
We've all done some things.

26:29.980 --> 26:33.507
Oh no, I can keep
my bags up front with me.

26:35.595 --> 26:38.578
Oh, no, it's not--
it's not for your bags.

26:38.598 --> 26:40.914
It's for you.

26:40.991 --> 26:43.008
-What?
-Yeah.

26:43.085 --> 26:47.846
I mean, if you want to go now,
that's the best that I can do.

26:47.998 --> 26:50.423
My badge means nothing
down here.

26:50.443 --> 26:52.517
I been working on this
all day--so has my supervisor.

26:52.670 --> 26:54.686
And honestly, it's gonna take
more than a day

26:54.763 --> 26:57.022
to go through the proper
channels to get you across.

26:57.099 --> 26:58.357
A whole bunch of departments

26:58.433 --> 27:01.343
have to sign off on me
getting you back, all right?

27:01.345 --> 27:04.179
So please,
please just be patient

27:04.181 --> 27:05.605
and give me a couple of days

27:05.625 --> 27:08.292
to get you across
through the proper channels.

27:08.443 --> 27:09.460
No.

27:09.611 --> 27:11.945
Luca's immune system
is still fragile.

27:11.964 --> 27:13.279
I need to be there with him.

27:13.374 --> 27:16.358
If anything goes wrong,
I have to be there.

27:16.377 --> 27:18.469
Can't your husband
or your sister-in-law

27:18.620 --> 27:20.453
take him to the doctor
if something happens?

27:20.473 --> 27:24.199
You don't get it.
I am the doctor.

27:24.201 --> 27:26.459
-I'll do it.
-Okay, okay. Whoa, whoa, stop.

27:26.537 --> 27:29.605
Wait, okay, just--
just let me think.

27:33.135 --> 27:35.319
-(sighs)
-I'll do it.

27:35.396 --> 27:37.112
Okay, I-I know.

27:42.069 --> 27:44.736
You know, I've been back
and forth across this border

27:44.813 --> 27:48.907
over a dozen times,
and I've never had a problem,

27:48.984 --> 27:50.709
but this is crazy,
even for me.

27:53.397 --> 27:54.380
Get in.

28:13.526 --> 28:15.442
What are you gonna say
if they find me?

28:16.362 --> 28:20.072
Whoops.
How'd she get in here?

28:27.206 --> 28:28.447
Sorry about the smell.

28:28.523 --> 28:31.125
I keep my gym clothes
back here.

28:35.789 --> 28:37.864
OFFICER:
Stop. Passport.

28:37.942 --> 28:39.341
<i> Buenas noches.</i>

28:42.947 --> 28:44.296
Don't flash me
your credentials.

28:44.372 --> 28:46.039
I asked for your passport.

28:46.116 --> 28:48.467
Sorry. My mistake.

28:48.543 --> 28:51.211
(dog barking)

28:51.288 --> 28:53.230
You're in Mexico
on FBI business?

28:53.307 --> 28:55.457
GARRETT:
No, no. Just a day trip.

28:55.459 --> 28:57.309
Just picking up some maracas
for the kids.

28:57.461 --> 29:00.645
Ate at that, um, what is that,
Tía Maria's Café?

29:00.798 --> 29:02.814
Just love it down here.

29:02.967 --> 29:04.057
That place rips off
tourists.

29:04.134 --> 29:05.150
Yeah, tell me about it.

29:05.302 --> 29:06.802
You got any firearms
in the car?

29:06.820 --> 29:07.652
No, sir.

29:07.821 --> 29:09.621
Unless my kid's
water pistols count.

29:11.992 --> 29:14.585
I'm gonna have you pull over
to secondary.

29:14.736 --> 29:15.978
It's right over there.

29:15.996 --> 29:17.829
GARRETT:
Look, man, I gotta report back

29:17.906 --> 29:19.331
to the field office.

29:19.483 --> 29:21.759
We really gotta do all this?
Hmm?

29:21.910 --> 29:23.485
Come on,
I'm a fellow man of the shield.

29:23.487 --> 29:25.721
We'll make it quick.
Just pull over.

29:27.157 --> 29:28.390
GARRETT:
All right.

29:36.667 --> 29:37.691
Would you pop the trunk,
sir?

29:40.354 --> 29:43.447
Excuse me, officer.
Can I speak to your supervisor?

29:43.598 --> 29:45.098
(dog barking)

29:45.175 --> 29:48.076
(officer speaking Spanish)

29:50.180 --> 29:52.438
-(dog barking)
-Easy, boy.

29:52.458 --> 29:53.499
Pop the trunk.

29:55.461 --> 29:57.185
Can you step out of the car,
please?

29:57.204 --> 29:59.630
(dog continues barking)

30:09.883 --> 30:11.366
(whistle trilling)

30:11.368 --> 30:13.459
We have a woman
in the back.

30:13.479 --> 30:16.146
(dog barking)

30:16.298 --> 30:18.464
GARRETT:
I can explain.

30:18.484 --> 30:21.209
OFFICER: Are you all right?
Do you speak English?

30:21.211 --> 30:22.878
Are you okay?

30:22.896 --> 30:28.216
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:28.235 --> 30:29.475
Yeah.

30:29.553 --> 30:33.497
<i> (intense music)</i>

30:37.837 --> 30:39.336
OFFICER: Sir, go ahead,

30:39.563 --> 30:41.063
pull it over here.

30:41.081 --> 30:42.714
SECOND OFFICER:
Right over there.

30:46.679 --> 30:49.346
What's gonna happen to me?

30:49.423 --> 30:51.181
I'm sure my boss
or whoever's on their way down.

30:51.333 --> 30:53.575
They'll vouch for us,
then we'll be released.

30:53.577 --> 30:55.185
When?

30:55.262 --> 30:58.063
Tomorrow. Fingers crossed.

31:01.251 --> 31:02.526
When do I get a call?

31:04.363 --> 31:05.770
Thony, in case
you hadn't noticed,

31:05.847 --> 31:08.031
I'm behind
the same set of bars you are.

31:09.109 --> 31:11.184
I need to tell my family
what's going on.

31:11.203 --> 31:13.328
Your husband too?

31:15.190 --> 31:17.282
How much you tell him?
Hmm?

31:17.376 --> 31:19.126
You tell him about Arman?

31:21.105 --> 31:23.547
About me?

31:26.368 --> 31:29.444
Yeah, that's what I thought.

31:29.446 --> 31:36.184
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:51.559 --> 31:52.618
Nadia?

31:54.488 --> 31:56.229
Nadia.

31:56.323 --> 31:59.808
Hi. What happened?
Did you see Hayak?

31:59.810 --> 32:01.919
-Yeah.
-NADIA: And?

32:01.995 --> 32:03.979
I told him I thought
it was the Norteños

32:03.997 --> 32:05.664
who tried to kill me.

32:05.740 --> 32:07.983
He believed you?

32:08.001 --> 32:10.410
Well, he believed there
was still $6 million

32:10.487 --> 32:13.263
to be made if we sold
those guns to Noah.

32:13.340 --> 32:15.507
Once he heard that,
nothing else mattered.

32:15.583 --> 32:18.918
So all the money
we've worked for goes to Hayak?

32:18.938 --> 32:20.420
Again?

32:20.497 --> 32:22.330
God, is that all
you care about?

32:22.349 --> 32:23.589
Coming clean on this deal

32:23.667 --> 32:25.183
is the only thing
that's keeping me alive.

32:25.335 --> 32:28.487
(speaking Spanish)

32:29.840 --> 32:32.115
Everything I do, I do for you.

32:32.192 --> 32:35.193
Even after all those lies about
going to Mexico with her.

32:35.345 --> 32:37.955
(speaking Spanish)

32:38.031 --> 32:39.581
I'm sorry.

32:40.867 --> 32:43.535
Look, we make this deal
with Noah,

32:43.611 --> 32:45.629
we'll leave Vegas
like we planned.

32:49.134 --> 32:50.592
We'll start new lives.

33:00.479 --> 33:04.231
(phone buzzing)

33:09.896 --> 33:12.322
Oh, my God, Thony,
where are you?

33:12.549 --> 33:14.065
I've been held at the border.

33:14.218 --> 33:16.142
God...(stammering)

33:16.161 --> 33:18.996
Are you okay?
What happened to Garrett?

33:19.147 --> 33:20.555
He's in the cell with me.

33:20.557 --> 33:22.390
<i> FIONA:</i>
<i> What?</i>

33:22.409 --> 33:24.650
Everything's gonna be okay.

33:24.728 --> 33:26.628
We just don't know
when we're gonna be released.

33:28.340 --> 33:30.248
I need you to reach out
to Dara in the morning.

33:30.400 --> 33:33.844
Just make sure they're okay.
You're my one call, Fi.

33:33.995 --> 33:35.828
(sighs)
What do I tell Marco?

33:35.922 --> 33:37.255
<i> THONY:</i>
<i> Um, nothing.</i>

33:37.332 --> 33:38.515
<i> I'll deal with Marco</i>
<i> when I'm home.</i>

33:38.592 --> 33:40.925
I'll call you
as soon as I'm out.

33:41.078 --> 33:42.244
<i> Mahal kita.</i>

33:42.262 --> 33:44.312
<i> Mahal kita,</i> okay? Be safe.

33:48.085 --> 33:48.933
Tell me what?

33:49.086 --> 33:51.936
<i> (tense music)</i>

33:52.013 --> 33:53.438
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:53.532 --> 33:54.939
What's going on?

33:55.092 --> 33:56.867
Luca and Dara will be here
this morning,

33:57.018 --> 33:58.851
and Thony's still working
on getting back.

33:58.929 --> 34:00.686
Everything's gonna be okay.

34:00.764 --> 34:02.447
No, it's not.

34:02.599 --> 34:04.190
Just please--just don't
wake up the kids.

34:04.268 --> 34:05.934
You're my sister.

34:05.952 --> 34:07.452
You should be telling me
what's going on.

34:07.454 --> 34:09.788
Thony said she'll be home soon,
all right?

34:09.940 --> 34:11.439
-This isn't her home!
-Just--

34:11.441 --> 34:14.292
Home is in Manila with me!
With<i> nanay</i> and<i> tatay.</i>

34:14.294 --> 34:15.385
You remember them, Fiona?

34:15.537 --> 34:17.629
You couldn't get out
fast enough,

34:17.705 --> 34:19.556
but you gave our parents
nothing but trouble.

34:19.707 --> 34:20.949
I left for a lot of reasons,

34:20.951 --> 34:22.208
and one is the way<i> tatay</i>
spoke to me

34:22.286 --> 34:23.618
like the way
you're talking to me now.

34:23.637 --> 34:26.063
Drinking and running around
with boys from the time

34:26.214 --> 34:27.472
